==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Taconic
<hw>Ta*con"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Geol.)</fld>
<def>Designating, or pertaining to, the series of rocks forming the
<etsep>Taconic</etsep> mountains in Western New England. They were once
supposed to be older than the Cambrian, but later proved to belong to
the Lower Silurian and Cambrian.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tact</ent>⟦br⟧
